Feature: a forced reviewer-fail is fail-closed under fabro so no work_done complete ever reaches the wire

  Fabro DOT loop-graph fail-closed edges — ADR-051 (outcome-conditional fail-closed edges;
  emit_r-to-halt on outcome=failed), Anchored on ADR-048 (invariant #4: the shop-msg protocol
  is preserved). Evidence: findings/fabro-spike/05-structural-loop.md section 1(d) and the
  workflow-forcefail.fabro reference definition — a forced reviewer-fail gave run STATUS FAILED
  with wdg_r/emit_r never reached and no complete on the wire. Because emit_r (the sole gated
  emitter) is reachable only via review, signoff, wdg_r, a review node that does not sign off
  structurally cannot reach the emitter — the guarantee is ENFORCED by native script= scoping,
  not advisory. This is a LEAD-PROCESS contract pin with no current BC addressee; NOT
  dispatchable via assign_scenarios, flagged for the discriminator should a fabro-orchestration
  BC be created.
  @scenario_hash:7ddada412f406767
  Scenario: a forced reviewer-fail yields run status FAILED with the sole emitter never reached and no work_done complete on the wire
    Given a fabro run whose review node is forced to exit non-zero with outcome failed
    When the run reaches the review node
    Then the run terminates with status FAILED
    And the wdg_r and emit_r nodes are never reached
    And no work_done with status complete is deposited on the wire
